Dealing with outliers using IQR method¶

In this method we calculate the lower and upper quartiles and then calculate the interquartile range. All the values that do no lie in the range are omitted. We did this as per need on all the features in the given dataset.

Dealing with outliers in whole Dataset by removing upper and lower 1% percentile values¶
In [25]:
def cap_data(df):
    for col in df.columns:
        print("capping the ",col)
        if (((df[col].dtype)=='float64') | ((df[col].dtype)=='int64')):
            percentiles = df[col].quantile([0.01,0.99]).values
            df[col][df[col] <= percentiles[0]] = percentiles[0]
            df[col][df[col] >= percentiles[1]] = percentiles[1]
        else:
            df[col]=df[col]
    return df
